1.title: Motorboats and Mustard
1.plot: The new cast gets back together for an unforgettable Spring Break in Florida. No one wants to share a room with warring couple Bradley and Raven, while Hunter and Duke get in a heated competition over the new roommate, Kelsie.

2.title: Two Can Play at This Game
2.plot: Duke has to head home to be with family while the rest of the roommates explore St. Pete and Kelsie finds herself struggling as the new girl in the house.

3.title: Girl's Night!
3.plot: Raven and the girls head out for a wild night on the town away from Bradley and the boys. The roommates call Duke to check-up on him, though little do they know he has a surprise in the works for them.

4.title: Bringing Home the Bacon
4.plot: Bradley decides the best way to get over his recent breakup is to roast a pig for his roommates who are extremely skeptical of his "reverse oven" technique.

5.title: Three's a Crowd
5.plot: Karynda's love life seems to be heating up when she finds herself in the beginning of a love triangle with two guys from work. In the meantime, although Bradley and Raven say they're broken up, the housemates aren't so sure and Duke's confidence with the ladies may finally be paying off.

6.title: In and Out of Love
6.plot: The other Party Down South crew is back, and if you thought the party in Biloxi was crazy then get ready for even more country-fried antics even further south, in St. Petersburg, Florida.

7.title: Hot Tub Cry Machine
7.plot: Bradley attempts to rekindle his relationship with Raven, but as a result, he finds himself in a pool of tears, not once, but twice, maybe three times. The rest of the gang decide to head to the beach to get away from the drama. Little do they know, too much sun and booze with a little bit of Ashton will brew up a bigger storm.

8.title: Double Shot of Heartbreak
8.plot: Bradley and Raven's relationship finally reaches its breaking point, which leads to an epic guy's night and Duke reeling in two girls.

9.title: If the RV's A'Rockin', Don't Come A'Knockin'
9.plot: The gang takes an RV trip to the Mud Bog. Raven goes four-wheeling, Karynda and Ashton mud wrestle, Hunter and Kelsie make a serious decision about their relationship, and Duke gets caught between two girls.

10.title: Pie Fight!
10.plot: Arriving home from the mud bogs, Bradley's prank on Ashton backfires. Later, a little chocolate in the face suddenly turns from a pie fight to a cat fight. The cast say their goodbye's & a memorable Spring Break comes to an end.

1.title: I Don't Do Dibs
1.plot: The gang takes an RV trip to the Mud Bog. Raven goes four-wheeling, Karynda and Ashton mud wrestle, Hunter and Kelsie make a serious decision about their relationship, and Duke gets caught between two girls.

2.title: Feel the Burn
2.plot: It's the gang's first night out on the town and they get wild! Raven decides Tommy is not for her and sets her sights on Bradley. But Ashton is jealous that Raven is hooking up with all the guys in the house.

3.title: Strictly Cuddle Buddies
3.plot: Feelings are flying through the house and everyone is catching them, especially Ashton, Raven and Bradley. Only time (and a whole lot of drama) will tell who ends up with whom.

4.title: Three's a Party
4.plot: Bradley is in a bind after learning that Ashton and Raven both have feelings for him. The ensuing drama begins to wear on the rest of the gang and they let Bradley know he needs to make a decision... is it Raven or is it Ashton?

5.title: Bradley Who?
5.plot: Bradley chooses Raven as his boo thing, leaving Ashton in tears. But she perks up quickly when she meets a hunky blond at the local swimmin' hole.

6.title: The Boss' Daughter
6.plot: After Duke's dramatic fight to revive Ashton, she comes back ready to party it up like never before. The sexual frustration in the house finally reaches a boiling point and Magan makes her needs known to all. Just when you thought Tommy had learned his lesson about hooking up with Magan's friends, he makes it crystal clear... lesson not learned.

7.title: Sunday Funday
7.plot: After unwittingly bringing two girls back to the house, Tommy lands in hot water with Magan. Meanwhile, Duke lands in literal hot water with Magan's feisty friends, while the flirting and fighting between Bradley, Raven and Ashton finally boils over.

8.title: Fishin' for Trouble
8.plot: The gang goes on a fishing trip and things heat up between Tommy and Brittany, but will messing with the boss' daughter mean his job is on the line? Meanwhile, Ashton is in for one awkward boat ride with two guys she recently hooked up with, before she slips back into a bad habit that forces everyone to step in and save her.

9.title: Got Milk
9.plot: After an emotional house intervention, the roommates decide they need to get out of the house. So to celebrate the 4th of July and to get away from all the drama, the roommates head to the woods for some rafting, mudding and good old-fashioned patriotic redneck fun.

10.title: Roll with the Punches
10.plot: Bradley gets into a bar fight and might be going to jail, ending his summer of fun. Ashton really wants to move on from Tyler and finally decides to give Brandon a real chance. Raven goes back to her flirty ways and this pushes Bradley over the edge.

11.title: Meet My Dad, Brad
11.plot: After Bradley and Raven's blowout, "Hurricane Hunter" rallies the roommates on a mission to finish their keg. Magan goes toe to high-heeled toe with a feisty local. And when Raven's dad comes to visit, Bradley's attempt to win him over doesn't go remotely as planned.

12.title: The Wild Karynda
12.plot: The summer winds down as Duke and Karynda each embark on a mission to make out, Bradley and Raven take their relationship to the next level and the gang has one last wild night before the party ends and it's time to go home.

imdb.plot outline: Eight strangers live in a house together for a wild vacation. They must live with each other, work, and learn to accept other people along the way. The group emerge better people and find embark on new chapters in their life after leaving the house.
